ssage?topicID=143.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=143.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#000000><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#A0B0E0 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#A0B0E0 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ukarthanon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karthanon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.attbi.com/~james.martens/karth_head.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/6/02 12:04:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply</span><hr size=1> A stout dwarf who had been sitting back and smoking his pipe while inspecting some knucklebones looks up at the tall warriorlike individual and stands up, pocketing the knucklebones as he does so.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bah! So ready ta leave, are ya?&quot;, the dwarf sniffs. &quot;Some kinda patience ye have, then. What, goblins got yer tongue and ye wish ta get it back?&quot;.<br>
<br>
He raises his hand to the bartender and raises two fingers - the bartender nods and hands him two dwarven jacks full of Brell's Holy Ale - and he hands one to the person looking for Winyoung, and takes a deep swill of the ale and blows some foam from his beard before he speaks again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Take some time. Winyoung may not be 'ere right now, but I'm sure she be about somewheres. There's other's of us around now - I be Karthanon, a mid-seasoned dwarven warrior. My niece Kinmerya be abouts somewheres - a cleric. If ya want ta argue philosophy while yer waiting, I'm sure ya can argue knots with Gnostik, our local sage of th'Tears. Or maybe show us yer martial prowess 'gainst Kogbender th'Ogre, who might be hidin' in the shadows here or there.&quot;<br>
<br>
Karthanon glances back at the corner of the guildhall, where a wolfish tail twitches and then disappears out of sight, and scowls. &quot;Or, if yer not so lucky, you can get in a food fight with Salvia and her ilk...&quot;<br>
<br>
He gestures back at the table and the ale the man holds bemused in his hands. &quot;Get back over dere, drink that up, and then have a few more. Maybe once ya get yer fill and some some good food ye'll not be so impatient - there's times and place fer dat, dontcha know, and meetin' new friends and comrades in arms be not a time fer it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Karthanon scratches his beard, and then takes another gulp from his ale. &quot;'Though I ain't seen Winyoung around fer a while, except mayber fer a few seconds in th'Bazaar...&quot;<br>
<br>
/ooc (sort of) Welcome, dear sir! I'm sure one of the officers will speak with you, although they've been busy for a spell. (( Something called RL, who would've thunk it? )) Please, sit down and relax, I'm sure that someone will speak with you soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ukogbender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kogbender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ToV Elder</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/6/02 2:46:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply</span><hr size=1> *the door to the tavern pushes slowly open and a weary and battleworn (and stained) ogre walks into the Hall several feet and stops straighting himself he peers around the room  eyes pausing for a moment on the new face of a barbarian then continuing untill a he has made note of all here. Returning his gaze to the Barbarian drinking with Karth he makes his way to their table*<br>
<br>
&quot;Lo der frien Ralstaan... da Guard told mez yuu here az da applicant tu da Tears, it iz not our custom tu leave sumone wifout response and sitin in da tavern so long but der wuz tingz dat neded duin first...* the ogre makes a vauge gesture to his armor's stains and fresh dings and rents*   ifin yuu still interested mez hear yuu out now frien ....&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
*this said the ogre signals a servant to bring food and drink for  the three  and gently lowers himself into a chair what creaks ominously under the armored ogre, none to gently the Great Black Acrylia Halaberd  slides to the floor sticking in the floor blade down.. attesting to its sharpness...With a slightly anoyed expression Ralstaan  repeats his tale for the ogre .... the meal is brought and the ogre begins devouring platefulls of food... but his eyes never leave those of the barbarians and Ralstaan is sure the ogre has heard each word. As Ralstaan fineshes his tale the ogre pauses and takes a pitcher of ale .. pasing his stein compleetly to down it in one great gulp then refocuses himself on the barbarian*<br>
<br>
&quot; Da Lady Winyoung has spoke of yuu tu me before and speak guud tingz... yuu sound likie  da guud type tu meez an me tink yuu make a guud Tear.  Comez Hunt wif me suun and wez kin propurlu...prooper...bah, wez Makie yu da Tear den.&quot;<br>
<br>
*grabing a game bird from the table the ogre pops it whole into his mouth chewing it bones and all.. as he fineshes it  he rises from his seat... reaching to pull the Halaberd from the floor as he stands..*<br>
<br>
&quot;Frien Ralstaan, welcom tuu The Tears of Veeshan! Now, yuu mus scuze mez.. da week habz been long and the battles hab drained mez...mez go takie da baf and sleep fer two dayz. Der iz open roomz fer our kin in dat wing ub da Guild Hall, yu may take one az yerz an makie yuself at homez.  * a warm smile passes Kog's face and his next words are  quiet and gentle enough as to be heard by only Ralstaan.*an der ebun a few open next tuu Winyoung's ruum frien.&quot;<br>
<br>
*the barbarian grunts as the ogre flops a massive paw on his shoulder and pats it while beaming a smile down to him. Snatching a few of the remaining plates of food and a cask of Otijims the ogre wanders (none to steadily) towards the oposite wing of the Guild Hall, noding to greetings and speaking a word or two to a few folks...*<br>
<br>
