</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uralstaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ralstaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/6/02 10:56:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hehe doh</span><hr size=1> Ralstaan watches the battle-weary ogre stumble towards his quarters.  He looks at the rest of the on-lookers and makes out quiet elven whispers and dwarven grunts.  His hand still resting on his hilt he reaches for the Holy Ale and nods at the stout dwarven warrior, who by now has had three ales up in the count.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Before you go Kog&quot;, Ralstaan speaks in between a gulp.  &quot;I could never make out whether eating with an ogre makes makes a man hungrier or lose his appetite.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ralstaan looks around again and begins to make out a small hint of noise.  <br>
<br>
&quot;As to Gnostik I have nothing to offer by way of talk of religion, though the more of these Holy Ales I drink I may begin to take interest in the priesthood.  To Salvia I look forward to a food fight with you, so long as I get the ogre on my side.  To Karth you seem busy enough as is, what with that fine looking neice of yours to protect.  And to Winyoung.............well that is my business.&quot;<br>
<br>
The warrior stands and for the first time slacks from his grip and walks to Kogbender.  He lands a hand on the massive shoulder, not hard enough to cause dent or grimace, but hard enough to let him know that when he takes him up on his offer to hunt he will come prepared to fight.  <br>
Ralstaan makes his way to the wing of sleeping quarters and looks at each great door.  After the fourth door he comes to a room with a familiar flower hanging from it.  He remembers with a smile and quietly begins to press against the door.<br>
<br>
&quot;Barbarian fool.  Winyoung is a lady.  And if I have strength in me that is how she will stay.&quot;<br>
<br>
The warrior picks up his pack and makes his way to the farthest room, at the farthest end of the hall.<br>
<br>
<br>
