</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ussolaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ssolaria</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.ix.netcom.com/~ddodgers/ssol_face.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/6/02 4:09:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.ix.netcom.com/~ddodgers/ssol_face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply</span><hr size=1> In the courtyard in front of the guildhall a bright red portal forms turning  quickly to blue.  Once the portal solidifies, a Carmine robed High Elf steps through.  Moving quickly without a backwards glance Ssolaria strides into the guild hall.<br>
<br>
Heading to an empty table Ssolaria drops several bags of gems, opals, peridots, perls, and other less precious stones fill the tables, a veritable king's ransom.  Going through her packs Ssolaria removes a black bag that seems to radiate a tangible aura, malevolence and stronger emotions seem to emanate frome the little bag, darkness where the other bags seem to reflect all the colors of the rainbow from faceted faces of the gems.<br>
<br>
&quot;Dangit I hate going to Neriak, but that is the only place I can get the Soulstones that let us travel to the plane of Hate.  My agent there charges me a small fortune for each one of these and she has the nerve to charge me a &quot;service charge&quot; on top of the princely sum I pay for the stones.  oh well, we will make it back and then some I think.&quot;<br>
<br>
Taking notice of the other Tears in the guild hall she looks up and sees a strong fierce looking barbarian warrior.  Walking up to the new Warrior and Kogbender she approaches them warily.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who is this Koggie?  A new guildmate mayhap?&quot;  Ssolaria says with a sly look in her eye.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you are here to join us, then you must be marked as only the strong can survive a marking by Veeshan.  That is very good.  I need some strong warriors.  What do you think Kogbender can this pup stand up to the Maestro?  Think he has the fiber to head the attack on an Ashenbone Drake or 2?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I would see if you are indeed worthy of the title of Protector of our sweet sister Winyoung.  Come to the home of Innoruk with us tomorrow, if you are man enough!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Kogbender I know you can deal with the yard trash easily enough in Hate, lets welcome our newest member with a party in innoruks's music hall.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;GNOSTIK!  Where are you?&quot;  Ssolaria looks around for the stout defender of Brell's faith.  &quot;You signed up to join us, please extend the invitation to our allies in the Gathering please, I still have a million things to do to get ready.&quot;<br>
<br>
The sorceress sees her lover snoozing in her accostomed chair by the fire.  Poor dear she needs her rest, we will go and hunt Sunday I think.  off to Kaesoria to talk to Xalgoz agian.  Miserable shade that he is.<br>
<br>
&quot;On the morrow I will be back.  Meet us in Greater Feydark by the wizard spires.&quot;  Ssolaria says as she rushes off to her rooms and then running through a gate to the Emerald Jungle.<br>
